docstrings= test for code (of input/output of various fucntion and documentation for source code)
include docstrings under things to describe what they do

using docstrings to test programs! (if you have enough docstrings you'll be able to generate your own documentation!)

doctests
  >>> function(method)
expected result

>>>add(5,2)
7

it doesn't matter where your doctests are!
python  -m doctest [directory]
